E.8 verify (2026-05-13):

Live end-to-end against production proves the full draft → dry-run →
activate → delete lifecycle. Drafts don't register triggers; dry-run
dispatches a real worker run but quarantines mutating outbound calls
into `cloud_runs.dry_run_actions`; activate flips status + registers
triggers; delete archives + tears down.

Code lands:
  api/src/routes/automations.ts
    - CreateSchema gains `status` enum (default 'draft').
    - UpdateSchema gains optional `status`.
    - AutomationRow + every RETURNING/SELECT clause now carries `status`.
    - POST /v1/automations skips reconcileTriggers when row.status != 'active'.
    - PUT /v1/automations/:id: reconcile only on (now-)active; teardown
      on active→draft/archived transitions.
    - DELETE also sets status='archived' (alongside archived_at).
    - NEW POST /v1/automations/:id/dry-run: builds inputs from body OR
      triggerIndex+synthetic_payload (via the existing pickInputMapper),
      INSERTs cloud_runs with triggered_by='dry_run', dry_run=true,
      run_mode='test', dispatches via SQS. Returns
      { runId, dryRun:true, automationId, automationVersion,
        triggeredBy:'dry_run', previewPollUrl }.
    - NEW POST /v1/automations/:id/activate: flips draft→active +
      reconcileTriggers; idempotent on already-active (alreadyActive:true,
      no reconcile call); 404 on archived/missing.
    - NEW dryRunPreviewRoute (mounted at /v1/runs in app.ts):
      GET /v1/runs/:runId/dry-run-preview returns
      { runId, status, automationId, automationVersion, triggeredBy,
        startedAt, completedAt, dryRunActions, activity }. 400 on bad
      UUID, 404 on missing, 404 not_a_dry_run when row.dry_run=false.

  api/src/lib/browserbase.ts                — already patched in E.5
                                              (timeout-units + URL pref).

  worker/src/dry-run/interceptor.ts         — DryRunBuffer gained an
                                              optional flush hook so the
                                              `cloud_runs.dry_run_actions`
                                              column updates LIVE after
                                              every intercept (not just
                                              at SIGTERM teardown).
                                              flushBuffer + the new hook
                                              both use sql.json(value)
                                              for jsonb writes (memory:
                                              feedback_postgres_js_jsonb_use_sql_json).
  worker/src/dry-run/interceptor.test.ts    — flushBuffer tests updated
                                              to stub sql.json on the
                                              fake postgres-js client.
  worker/src/opencode-plugin/index.ts       — when ctx.dryRun, instantiates
                                              the buffer with a live-flush
                                              hook that UPDATEs the row.
                                              Teardown-time flush kept as
                                              durable backstop.

  api/src/app.ts                            — mounts dryRunPreviewRoute
                                              under /v1/runs (existing
                                              requireWorkspaceJwt covers it).

  api/src/routes/automations.test.ts        — 14 new test cases:
                                              CREATE default-draft (no
                                              reconcile) + CREATE active
                                              (reconcile fires); activate
                                              404/409/idempotent/happy;
                                              dry-run dispatch + trigger-
                                              index + 404; preview 401/
                                              400/404/not_a_dry_run/200.

