In-step debugging summary:
  - Run #1: dry_run row created but no LLM activity. Caused by the warm
    pool still holding pre-E.7 image (digest 4cefa1d…). Stopped that
    task; subsequent dispatches went to the new image.
  - Run #2: LLM ran, called send_sms → approval gate fired (still old
    image). Stopped warm pool again; pool autoscaler spawned fresh
    tasks on basics-worker:e8-…
  - Run #5: interceptor fired (dry_run_action event present), buffer
    captured the send_sms intent, but cloud_runs.dry_run_actions stayed
    [] because the teardown-time flush only runs on SIGTERM (15-min
    idle stop). Added a live-flush hook on DryRunBuffer; pushed e8b.
  - Run #6 (first attempt with live flush): dry_run_actions was written,
    but as a JSONB STRING SCALAR not an array — the
    ${JSON.stringify(v)}::jsonb double-encoding bug from MEMORY.md.
    Swapped both flushBuffer and the live-flush hook to use sql.json(v);
    pushed e8c.
  - Run #6 (final after e8c drain): jsonb_typeof='array', count=1,
    entry shape matches DryRunActionEntry. Spec verify clauses met.

